Project Title: Library Management System

Project Description:

The Library Management System is a Python-based application designed to manage books in a library. The system allows users to add, view, search, update, delete, issue, and return books through a menu-driven interface.

Purpose:

The purpose of this project is to demonstrate the use of Python programming, database management using SQLite, and software development practices commonly used in open-source projects.

Main Features:

* Add books
* View books
* Search books
* Update book information
* Delete books
* Issue books
* Return books

Input:

* Book title
* Author name
* Quantity
* Book ID

Output:

* Updated book records
* Search results
* Success/error messages

Tools and Libraries:

* Python 3
* SQLite3

Usefulness:

The project helps libraries maintain book records efficiently and provides practical experience with Python and database operations.
